[normal]Pharmaceutical incentives [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Inclusion of other microbes[bold]The growing number of effective antiviral drugs in use
[normal] also illustrate
[normal]s
[normal] this point
[normal]. In many cases their development has been catalysed by the HIV pandemic, but these are finding application in the treatment of importan
[normal]t persistent viral pathogens in addition to HIV, such as 
[normal]h
[normal]epatitis C. New antivirals against influenza virus are also being used at the population level. This increasing and widespread use of antiviral drugs will inevitably be accompanied by the growing em
[normal]ergence of AMR in viruses (as already seen for HIV).
[normal] 
[normal]Thus many of the proposals outlined in the strategy may be equally applied to responses to resistance in organisms besides bacteria, and these should be given appropriate weighting in the strategy’s obj
[normal]ectives. 
[normal] 
[normal]For brevity, we have not addressed each aspect of AMR (such as
[normal] occurrences in
[normal] virology
[normal], mycology and 
[normal]parasitology) in detail individually in this response, but would be willing to provide further information to the committee 
[normal]if 
[normal]request
[normal]ed
[normal].  
